21    /**
22    * Object that contains baseline configuration for serialization
23    * process. An instance is owned by {@link ObjectMapper}, which
24    * passes an immutable instance for serialization process to
25    * {@link SerializerProvider} and {@link SerializerFactory}
26    * (either directly, or through {@link ObjectWriter}.
27    *<p>
28    * Note that instances are considered immutable and as such no copies
29    * should need to be created for sharing; all copying is done with
30    * "fluent factory" methods.
31    * Note also that unlike with Jackson 1, these instances can not be
32    * assigned to {@link ObjectMapper}; in fact, application code should
33    * rarely interact directly with these instance (unlike core Jackson code)
34    */
